.TH "exe2adf" "1" "2019-12-21" "exe2adf \[lq]User Manual\[rq]" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
exe2adf - convert Amiga executables to ADF disk images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]exe2adf\f[R] \f[B]-i\f[R] \f[I]filename.exe\f[R]
[\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]exe2adf\f[R] converts Amiga executable (\f[B].exe\f[R]) files into
bootable ADF (Amiga Disk File) disk images, suitable for use with Amiga
emulators or real hardware.
.PP
Created by Bonefish of the demo group Reality and released in 2015, the
tool places the executable onto a bootable floppy image with optional
support for boot-time text display, custom disk labels, directory
inclusion, custom bootblocks, and palette configuration.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Mandatory
.TP
\f[B]-i\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R], \f[B]\[en]input\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]
Amiga executable file to convert to ADF.
.SS Optional
.TP
\f[B]-a\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R], \f[B]\[en]adf\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]
Output ADF filename.
.TP
\f[B]-t\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R], \f[B]\[en]txt\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]
Text file to display at boot time.
.TP
\f[B]-l\f[R] \f[I]label\f[R], \f[B]\[en]label\f[R] \f[I]label\f[R]
Label of the ADF disk.
.TP
\f[B]-k\f[R], \f[B]\[en]add21k\f[R]
Free 21 KB before loading the rest of the floppy.
.TP
\f[B]-c\f[R], \f[B]\[en]cls\f[R]
Clear the screen before displaying the text file.
Only usable with \f[B]\[en]txt\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-w\f[R], \f[B]\[en]wide\f[R]
Set AmigaDOS/CLI to 80 columns instead of the default 60 columns.
.TP
\f[B]-p\f[R] \f[I]colors\f[R], \f[B]\[en]palette\f[R] \f[I]colors\f[R]
Set AmigaDOS/CLI palette.
Accepts 3 or 7 comma-separated RGB hex triplets:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
color 1: background (mandatory)
.IP \[bu] 2
color 2: foreground (mandatory)
.IP \[bu] 2
color 3: minimise icon
.IP \[bu] 2
color 4: cursor
.IP \[bu] 2
color 5: pointer main
.IP \[bu] 2
color 6: pointer shadow
.IP \[bu] 2
color 7: pointer highlight
.RE
.TP
\f[B]-d\f[R] \f[I]directory\f[R], \f[B]\[en]directory\f[R] \f[I]directory\f[R]
Directory to include on the floppy.
.TP
\f[B]-b\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R], \f[B]\[en]bootblock\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]
Install a custom bootblock.
.TP
\f[B]-0\f[R]
Show the sector allocation map.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Fast usage:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
exe2adf -i intro.exe
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Simple usage:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
exe2adf -i intro.exe -l myfloppy -a floppy.adf
exe2adf --input intro.exe --label myfloppy --adf floppy.adf
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Advanced usage:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
exe2adf -i intro.exe -l myfloppy -t readme.txt -a floppy.adf -k -c
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Palette usage (CLI colors only):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
exe2adf -i intro.exe -t readme.txt -a floppy.adf -p 000,fff,00f,f0f
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Palette usage (CLI and pointer colors):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
exe2adf -i intro.exe -t readme.txt -a floppy.adf \[rs]
        -p 000,fff,00f,f0f,888,444,fff
\f[R]
.fi
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
